    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent core, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (75.76) and **Junior Caminero** (73.35), who represent our highest-upside plays. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a massive 14% park adjustment against a vulnerable arm in Freeland, while **Junior Caminero** leverages a favorable matchup against Assad, where his elite 19% SP skill boost makes him a must-start despite a minor park penalty. **Trea Turner** (71.83) and **Kyle Schwarber** (69.61) are also locked into strong status, both seeing their profiles elevated by favorable wind conditions and, in the case of **Trea Turner**, a valuable leadoff spot against Ray. Meanwhile, **Colt Keith** (67.82) earns a spot in the top tier thanks to a prime leadoff position and a distinct platoon advantage that creates a significant efficiency gap over his base projection.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, who carried a score of 40.21. While the wind-out bonus pushed his floor, he ultimately fell short of our daily efficiency threshold because the matchup against S\u00e1nchez presents too much downward pressure on his expected production compared to our active starters. Among the active group, **Victor Scott II** (51.62) remains a critical inclusion due to the scarcity of stolen bases; despite the 8% penalty from batting ninth, his contribution to our league-leading pursuit of speed makes him indispensable. Investors should monitor the status of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (56.38); although he is cleared for the lineup, the 15% SP skill penalty against Englert serves as a warning that his ceiling is capped today. We continue to hold **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Logan O'Hoppe**, and **Luis Pena** in reserve as we balance game caps against today\u2019s projected output.",
